WEBVTT

01:11.195 --> 01:14.031
Write slip twice. Put money in the bag.

01:14.532 --> 01:15.532
Joe?

01:16.825 --> 01:17.701
Gina.

01:19.203 --> 01:22.038
Lucas, what are you doing in here?

01:22.956 --> 01:25.625
My life has reached its pinnacle.

01:28.545 --> 01:30.672
Joe's letting me close the store tonight.

01:30.964 --> 01:33.383
- You're kidding.
- I am not.

01:33.466 --> 01:35.385
Big responsibility, Lucas.

01:35.468 --> 01:36.344
Yes.

01:36.510 --> 01:39.012
But Joe's rules are extremely simple:

01:39.137 --> 01:40.889
Count money twice...

01:40.973 --> 01:43.016
keep my hands off of his beer...

01:43.225 --> 01:44.643
cigars...

01:44.851 --> 01:46.228
and drumsticks.

01:46.311 --> 01:49.356
My, my, how will you remember it all?

01:49.982 --> 01:51.066
Good luck.

01:51.149 --> 01:52.567
Don't screw it up.

01:56.570 --> 01:59.532
A responsibility like this
requires the obedience...

01:59.699 --> 02:01.117
of a saint.

02:37.651 --> 02:40.778
"Music Town
franchise option agreement"?

02:57.794 --> 02:59.463
They've got to be kidding.

03:01.590 --> 03:04.092
In the immortal words of The Doors:

03:05.761 --> 03:07.971
"The time to hesitate is through."

04:25.794 --> 04:26.878
Twenty-two.

04:27.504 --> 04:29.171
Twenty-two black.

04:30.798 --> 04:32.341
Who was that guy?

04:33.884 --> 04:36.303
Craps! End of roll! New roller!

04:37.763 --> 04:40.516
Place your bets, please.
Get your bets down.

04:41.809 --> 04:43.352
We have a high roller.

04:43.394 --> 04:46.855
$9,104. I counted it. Twice.

04:47.856 --> 04:49.315
I like your style.

04:50.483 --> 04:52.777
Joe told me to count it twice.

04:53.111 --> 04:55.864
No more bets, please. Put your bets down.

04:57.031 --> 04:59.199
Do I just throw it and get a seven?

04:59.241 --> 05:01.660
- That would be very good, sir.
- Feeling lucky?

05:01.744 --> 05:04.163
I'm guided by a force
much greater than luck.

05:05.164 --> 05:06.123
Seven!

05:06.206 --> 05:07.624
A winner!

05:07.708 --> 05:10.586
- Baby, you are sexy!
- I know.

05:11.170 --> 05:12.713
Same lucky shooter.

05:12.754 --> 05:14.465
Get your bets down.

05:14.755 --> 05:18.009
- Hot shooter on the line.
- You know what? Let it ride.

05:20.762 --> 05:22.263
Hot dice coming out.

05:22.388 --> 05:25.975
That's an $18,000 bet.
Sure you know what you're doing, kid?

05:26.184 --> 05:29.061
I know this: That if I win this roll...

05:29.145 --> 05:31.813
I will save the place that I work
from being sold...

05:31.897 --> 05:34.357
and the jobs of my friends that work there.

05:34.774 --> 05:37.152
Thus striking a blow at all that is evil...

05:37.277 --> 05:40.030
and making this world
a better place to live in.

05:40.280 --> 05:41.281
What?

05:43.950 --> 05:46.076
And I'll... buy you guys a drink.

05:46.118 --> 05:47.620
Party! Okay!

05:47.870 --> 05:49.288
Get your bets down.

05:49.455 --> 05:50.623
Joe...

05:51.749 --> 05:53.250
this one's for you.

05:55.711 --> 05:56.587
Two.

05:56.629 --> 05:58.380
- Craps.
- End of roll.

05:58.464 --> 06:01.008
You know something?
You used to be cute.

06:01.342 --> 06:03.593
And you used to have $9,000.

06:07.305 --> 06:10.099
I wonder if I'll be held responsible for this.

06:20.317 --> 06:22.402
What the hell are you doing here, man?

06:23.111 --> 06:26.073
Something happened to me last night
in Atlantic City.

06:26.448 --> 06:27.824
You went to Atlantic City?

06:27.991 --> 06:29.451
Did you win anything?

06:31.161 --> 06:32.995
No. I did not win.

06:33.871 --> 06:36.999
So, if you guys ever wonder
if it was nice to know you...

06:37.166 --> 06:39.502
I tell you, now, that it was.

06:40.169 --> 06:41.963
Shit, man, what happened?

06:42.839 --> 06:44.006
What happened?

06:44.090 --> 06:48.260
I do not regret the things I've done,
but those I did not do.

06:49.135 --> 06:50.762
Lucas, how much?

06:51.012 --> 06:52.180
How much?

06:55.684 --> 06:56.643
Shit.

06:57.853 --> 06:59.980
What do you mean by "shit"? What's up?

07:02.524 --> 07:06.277
Lucas doesn't have any money,
and Joe let him close the store last night.

07:06.360 --> 07:07.695
Yeah? So?

07:10.656 --> 07:13.742
I guess he didn't live up
to his responsibility, did he?

07:14.034 --> 07:17.162
No, not the full responsibility. Shut up.

07:17.538 --> 07:18.998
What's up, Joe?

07:21.332 --> 07:23.459
What's up with the boss threads, man?

07:24.168 --> 07:27.297
- Frigging Rex Manning Day.
- What's up with the hostility?

07:42.060 --> 07:43.061
Phone.

07:43.812 --> 07:47.065
Right. Empire Records,
open till midnight. This is Mark.

07:48.525 --> 07:49.901
It's the bank.

07:53.487 --> 07:54.655
Yeah, it's Joe.

07:56.240 --> 07:57.450
Are you sure?

07:58.492 --> 07:59.911
It should be.

08:00.244 --> 08:02.163
Empire Records, open till midnight.
This is Mark.

08:02.246 --> 08:03.914
I don't know. I'll have to check.

08:03.998 --> 08:06.082
- It's the boss.
- Give me a sec, please.

08:08.418 --> 08:11.963
Yeah, Mitch. Will you stop yelling, please?

08:12.255 --> 08:13.506
What's wrong?

08:14.424 --> 08:15.717
What is it?

08:16.468 --> 08:18.595
Lucas? No way. Come on.

08:19.929 --> 08:21.222
Here he comes.

08:44.118 --> 08:45.620
Damn it, Lucas!

08:51.876 --> 08:53.251
What's the matter?

08:57.297 --> 09:00.133
- Surprise!
- What is it?

09:00.217 --> 09:02.219
Happy Rex Manning Day.

09:02.469 --> 09:04.805
When did you have time to make these?

09:04.930 --> 09:07.975
Dad says there are 24 usable hours
in every day. Thank you.

09:08.432 --> 09:11.060
You absolutely amaze me. You are a nerd.

09:11.268 --> 09:12.395
That's me.

09:15.898 --> 09:17.733
- So?
- So.

09:18.693 --> 09:19.985
So today...

09:20.152 --> 09:23.988
- I will offer myself to Rex Manning.
- All right!

09:25.573 --> 09:26.574
I love you.

09:27.575 --> 09:28.702
Like this.

09:29.327 --> 09:31.579
Get your tongue off my record.

09:33.873 --> 09:36.960
Do you think Rex is the right guy
for my first time?

09:38.962 --> 09:42.006
I think he's perfect for you, Corey.

09:46.343 --> 09:48.095
I need to ask your advice.

09:48.178 --> 09:52.099
You know a lot about love
and women and that sort of thing.

09:52.307 --> 09:56.352
My wife left me for another woman, and
my girlfriend made me leave at gunpoint.

09:56.686 --> 09:59.105
- Does this qualify me?
- Definitely.

09:59.897 --> 10:03.860
I've decided today's the day
that I'll tell Corey how I feel about her.

10:04.110 --> 10:06.529
I know what you're thinking,
but I really am.

10:06.612 --> 10:10.199
I've been working here off and on
for five years, so...

10:10.741 --> 10:12.993
I've got to tell her how I feel.

10:13.243 --> 10:14.369
That I...

10:15.787 --> 10:16.955
Love her.

10:17.873 --> 10:19.541
How do I do that?

10:21.710 --> 10:23.295
You say, "I love you."

10:23.795 --> 10:25.714
You want written instructions?

10:27.089 --> 10:29.842
If I find that kid, I swear I'll kill him.

10:30.509 --> 10:32.219
- I'll tell her this morning.
- Good.

10:32.303 --> 10:34.138
By noon. Definitely.

10:34.221 --> 10:35.681
No. By noon or 1:00.

10:36.474 --> 10:38.893
By 1:37 exactly, Joe.

10:41.395 --> 10:42.604
Good luck.

10:43.063 --> 10:44.189
Thank you.

10:51.905 --> 10:55.200
I remember the first time he sang it
on The Family Way.

10:55.241 --> 10:58.285
I got so excited I almost choked
on a pretzel.

10:58.368 --> 10:59.787
- Don't go in there.
- Why?

10:59.870 --> 11:03.916
I got something to tell you. Both of you.

11:04.416 --> 11:07.753
Come on, Lucas, pick up the phone.
Pick it up.

11:08.504 --> 11:10.172
Come on, buckethead!

11:10.923 --> 11:12.132
Hi, Joe.

11:12.633 --> 11:15.343
- Does Joe know?
- Nope. Just act normal.

11:16.385 --> 11:17.804
- What's up, Joe?
- What's new?

11:17.887 --> 11:19.764
- How you doing?
- Damn!

11:20.556 --> 11:21.766
I got green!

11:21.849 --> 11:24.185
Let's see who goes first. I got a brown!

11:24.560 --> 11:26.604
- Anybody got brown?
- Brown.

11:27.688 --> 11:28.814
Orange.

11:30.649 --> 11:31.817
Shit!

12:30.247 --> 12:32.957
- What are you doing, man?
- Exercising my veto, man.

12:33.082 --> 12:35.710
It's only 9:00.
You sure you want to do that?

12:35.793 --> 12:38.170
Listening to this crap
will make you sterile.

12:40.756 --> 12:42.800
Maybe I want to be sterile.

12:51.016 --> 12:52.434
What are you doing here?

12:52.601 --> 12:56.271
Calculus. I hate it,
but my dad says I've got to get an A.

12:56.688 --> 12:58.815
You're not on until this afternoon.

13:00.192 --> 13:01.985
It's Rex Manning Day.

13:03.819 --> 13:05.404
Rex Manning Day.

13:05.988 --> 13:09.158
Oh, Rexy, you're so sexy.

13:46.235 --> 13:48.903
Mark, could you please not sing?

13:50.863 --> 13:52.323
You know what, Joe?

13:52.406 --> 13:55.368
One of these days,
I'm going to show you little people.

13:55.409 --> 13:58.704
On that day,
I'll jump out of my wheelchair and dance.

13:58.829 --> 14:00.247
How about today?

14:00.331 --> 14:01.874
Rex Manning Day.

14:12.717 --> 14:15.095
- Where's the money?
- The money is gone.

14:15.220 --> 14:17.013
Yeah, I know it's gone.

14:17.722 --> 14:18.682
Where's it gone to?

14:19.182 --> 14:20.599
Atlantic City.

14:21.767 --> 14:23.185
Is it coming back from Atlantic City?

14:24.853 --> 14:26.272
I don't think so.

14:26.605 --> 14:28.774
What's it doing in Atlantic City?

14:29.108 --> 14:30.484
Recirculating.

14:38.950 --> 14:40.243
Are you pissed off?

14:43.955 --> 14:45.456
Lucas, listen to me.

14:45.665 --> 14:49.252
I told Mitchell Beck
that you forgot to deposit the money.

14:49.627 --> 14:51.837
I told him the money was still here.

14:51.920 --> 14:54.798
Joe, that's not true. It's in Atlantic City.

14:55.507 --> 14:56.591
I swear.

14:58.927 --> 15:01.179
Shut up, sit down, and don't you move.

15:01.471 --> 15:04.558
- It could be in other cities by now.
- Shut up!

15:04.975 --> 15:09.270
Under no circumstances do I want you
to leave that couch.

15:10.646 --> 15:13.024
Unless it's to get me $9,000.

15:13.399 --> 15:15.359
Then you bring it here to me.

15:20.614 --> 15:22.116
I think it'll be okay.

15:22.490 --> 15:24.159
What makes you think that?

15:24.534 --> 15:27.787
Who knows where thoughts come from?
They just appear.

15:30.331 --> 15:31.583
What a moron.

15:35.128 --> 15:37.339
- Are you Corey Mason?
- For me?

15:38.088 --> 15:39.173
Thank you.

15:39.548 --> 15:40.632
Later.
- 'Bye, thank you.

15:41.508 --> 15:45.012
"To the number one in her class.
Harvard, 1999.

15:45.512 --> 15:48.849
"Make me proud. Love, Daddy."
That's sweet.

15:48.974 --> 15:51.143
God, nothing's ever enough for him.

15:51.477 --> 15:55.146
He didn't mean it like that.
I'm sure he didn't.

15:55.521 --> 15:56.773
Excuse me.

15:58.357 --> 16:00.109
Hi. How are you today?

16:32.932 --> 16:34.308
Hi, Debra.

16:37.436 --> 16:40.772
- She hates me.
- Yeah, she hates me, too.

16:41.272 --> 16:44.067
But I have enough sense to hate her back.

16:48.196 --> 16:49.656
- Good morning, Deb.
- Hi, Deb.

16:57.955 --> 16:59.415
Lucas, are you in trouble?

17:00.249 --> 17:01.875
Did you need the money?

17:02.751 --> 17:05.421
If you are in trouble, you can talk to me.
You know that.

17:06.088 --> 17:10.008
We're all in some kind of trouble.
Am I the only one who sees it?

17:10.843 --> 17:12.385
You know, Deb's in trouble.

17:13.803 --> 17:16.097
- A.J.'s in trouble.
- A.J.'s not in trouble.

17:16.180 --> 17:17.890
And Corey is in trouble.

17:17.973 --> 17:19.684
She's not in trouble.
She's going to Harvard.

17:19.767 --> 17:21.477
Mark's in trouble. Eddie's in trouble...

17:21.560 --> 17:23.938
Hey, I'm the one who's in trouble here.

17:24.396 --> 17:25.731
'Cause every minute that goes by...

17:25.772 --> 17:28.942
and I don't call the cops
I look like a bigger bananahead.

17:29.025 --> 17:33.238
Joe, I can categorically say
that you are not a bigger bananahead.

17:33.947 --> 17:36.074
You screwed me, Lucas.
You know that, right?

17:36.324 --> 17:37.617
What do you want me to do?

17:37.701 --> 17:41.580
- Call Mitchell? Tell him I lied?
- It seems like a viable option.

17:42.997 --> 17:46.208
I swear to God,
if you're fooling with me, I will kill you.

17:51.297 --> 17:54.133
- A.J., I need another closer.
- I opened, man.

17:54.425 --> 17:55.885
Come on. I wouldn't ask...

17:56.302 --> 17:58.137
but I have got no choice.

17:58.303 --> 17:59.596
I can close.

18:01.848 --> 18:03.808
Yeah, I can close. It's cool.

18:04.058 --> 18:06.686
They just raised my rent,
so I could use the money.

18:06.978 --> 18:08.605
Damn the man!

18:08.938 --> 18:11.399
Oh, God, I am in hell!

19:36.395 --> 19:40.274
You think it's possible for someone to be in
love with someone else and not even know it?

19:41.817 --> 19:45.320
In this life,
there are nothing but possibilities.

19:47.321 --> 19:48.489
That's good.

19:48.906 --> 19:51.534
I must tell Corey I love her by 1:37.

19:52.618 --> 19:54.245
That's an excellent time.

20:03.295 --> 20:06.006
You did have hair
when you went in there, right?

20:06.089 --> 20:08.758
It's still in the sink if you want to glue it.

20:11.511 --> 20:14.180
Is it true you committed
the perfect crime?

20:15.140 --> 20:16.850
Not entirely perfect.

20:20.102 --> 20:21.228
You see that, man?

20:25.566 --> 20:28.485
- What's with you today?
- Bad hair day.

20:29.111 --> 20:31.071
No, I mean with this. What is this?

20:32.281 --> 20:35.408
- What happened?
- I went to rock and roll heaven...

20:35.491 --> 20:38.620
and I wasn't on the guest list.
Now please move, I have to go to work.

20:39.579 --> 20:42.040
No. Now you tell me what is going on!

20:42.957 --> 20:47.420
I decided I'd rather kill myself than meet
Rex Manning. Excuse me, I'm going.

20:47.545 --> 20:49.963
Listen to me, this isn't funny.
I'm not joking.

20:50.172 --> 20:52.716
I won't let you leave
until you tell me what's going on.

20:53.008 --> 20:55.260
- Mind your own business.
- She's fine.

20:56.261 --> 20:57.721
She's amazing.

21:00.182 --> 21:01.266
Thank you.

21:03.477 --> 21:05.020
She's in the store.

21:05.353 --> 21:07.021
She's going to be okay.

21:08.356 --> 21:09.690
What's with you?
Yesterday you were normal...

21:09.815 --> 21:13.194
today you're like the Chinese guy
from The Karate Kid.

21:14.820 --> 21:16.614
What's with you today?

21:16.989 --> 21:19.033
What's with "today" today?

21:21.326 --> 21:22.619
I don't know.

21:35.006 --> 21:36.507
Why'd you do that?

21:36.590 --> 21:39.635
I'm just your typical nutty teenager
in America.

21:39.843 --> 21:42.388
Before you hear all about it...

21:44.139 --> 21:45.641
That's supposed to be a joke, right?

21:46.016 --> 21:47.601
No. You're the joke.

21:57.485 --> 21:59.862
Well, Sinead O'Rebellion...

22:00.780 --> 22:04.200
shock me, shock me, shock me
with that deviant behavior.

22:04.909 --> 22:08.662
That is so clever. You get smarter
the shorter your skirt gets.

22:08.870 --> 22:13.333
And you get smarter
the shorter your hair gets...
so it's probably a good thing
you went with that.

22:13.792 --> 22:16.294
- It's a wonderful look for you, darling.
- Thank you.

22:46.865 --> 22:48.783
I have to go to the bathroom.

22:50.743 --> 22:52.871
I want to report a robbery.

22:53.413 --> 22:54.955
No, I will not hold...

23:07.509 --> 23:08.719
Excuse me.

23:09.428 --> 23:10.595
Excuse me.

23:13.973 --> 23:15.308
Veto!

23:16.184 --> 23:17.769
What's up with that?

23:17.852 --> 23:20.980
It's too early.
It makes the customers all crazy-like.

23:21.230 --> 23:22.899
That's the whole point.

23:23.941 --> 23:24.901
Eddie!

23:24.942 --> 23:27.527
What's up, dude?
I heard your music playing.

23:27.611 --> 23:29.779
- That's pretty scary stuff.
- Yeah, it was moshy.

23:30.197 --> 23:33.241
I'm glad to say I made you
a tape last night, for educational purposes.

23:34.159 --> 23:37.829
Here's the deal.
You start off with a little classical music.

23:38.830 --> 23:41.790
Then you got some Shaggs on there,
and Residents...

23:42.208 --> 23:45.044
- and a little Floyd and Zeppelin.
- Floyd is very cool.

23:45.127 --> 23:48.255
And another very cool thing is,
I made you these.

23:49.048 --> 23:51.967
They're my special recipe
and you know what that means.

23:52.009 --> 23:53.260
Lots of sugar.

23:54.261 --> 23:56.971
You got to understand something here.

23:57.472 --> 23:59.933
This music is the glue of the world.

24:00.016 --> 24:02.685
It holds it all together. Without this...

24:03.269 --> 24:05.480
life would be meaningless.

24:06.272 --> 24:08.399
Dude, have you heard about Lucas?

24:12.986 --> 24:17.241
Lucas, man, I heard you went to Vegas
and married a mobster's wife...

24:17.324 --> 24:20.452
and now you've got a hit on you.
Is that true?

24:21.411 --> 24:23.330
Not entirely true.

24:24.373 --> 24:26.625
Outlaw Man, we salute you.

24:26.833 --> 24:27.917
Thank you.

24:28.167 --> 24:31.712
- No problem.
- This song goes out to our employee of the week, Lucas.

24:32.004 --> 24:33.297
A little tribute, man.

25:12.710 --> 25:14.295
What the hell's this?

25:15.920 --> 25:18.882
"Rules and standards
for Music Town employee conduct"?

25:19.716 --> 25:21.342
Put these in the boxes.

25:21.467 --> 25:24.679
- Music Town? We're not a Music Town.
- No, we're not a Music Town...

25:25.847 --> 25:26.806
yet.

25:26.973 --> 25:28.474
Isn't Music Town a chain?

25:28.683 --> 25:32.352
- "No gum chewing will be allowed inside the store"?
- They're turning us into a Music Town?

25:32.477 --> 25:35.689
- Why didn't you tell us?
- Because I was trying to stop it.

25:35.731 --> 25:37.190
What do you mean?

25:37.232 --> 25:40.694
I got enough money to make Mitch an offer.
He was going to make me a partner.

25:41.737 --> 25:43.322
I could have bought him out, eventually.

25:43.405 --> 25:44.406
You were going to buy Empire?

25:44.489 --> 25:46.949
- That's a good thing, right?
- That'll be fantastic.

25:47.992 --> 25:50.036
Do you think it'll happen now?

25:50.536 --> 25:52.788
I must pay for what Mr. Brilliant did.

25:52.872 --> 25:55.583
- It's over, kids, okay?
- Mitchell is the man.

25:56.417 --> 25:58.544
And "the man" calls all the shots.

25:58.628 --> 26:00.212
Damn the man.

26:01.546 --> 26:03.256
Let me explain it to you.

26:03.590 --> 26:06.217
Mitchell's the man, I'm the idiot...

26:06.593 --> 26:09.554
and you're the screw-up,
and we're all losers.

26:10.096 --> 26:11.765
Welcome to Music Town.

26:21.607 --> 26:23.192
"No visible tattoos."

26:23.275 --> 26:24.902
"No revealing clothing."

26:25.861 --> 26:27.321
We're both screwed.

26:27.947 --> 26:29.823
At least you're used to it.

26:30.032 --> 26:31.992
No, Debra, don't be bitter.

26:32.242 --> 26:34.994
With your ever-growing collection of...

26:35.078 --> 26:37.705
flesh-mutilating silver appendages...

26:37.830 --> 26:41.668
and your brand-new
neo-Nazi boot-camp makeover...

26:41.876 --> 26:45.588
- the boys will come running.
- Let's not fight, let's just rip.

26:50.133 --> 26:52.177
But we mustn't dwell.

26:52.928 --> 26:54.304
No, not today.

26:56.139 --> 26:57.265
We can't!

27:02.604 --> 27:04.438
Not on Rex Manning Day.

28:20.802 --> 28:23.262
Is it okay if I leave the couch,
'cause I'm leaving the couch, okay?

28:24.346 --> 28:28.017
