Bye, Gina.

01:13:37.383 --> 01:13:38.926
Yeah, don't drop the soap.

01:13:39.969 --> 01:13:41.596
I got to call Mitchell.

01:13:49.311 --> 01:13:51.229
It's $1,900.

01:13:51.896 --> 01:13:53.898
- I sold my Vespa across the street.
- No.

01:13:55.191 --> 01:13:58.653
Here's $600 left over
from the Rex Manning expense account.

01:13:59.154 --> 01:14:00.238
Cool.

01:14:00.530 --> 01:14:03.074
There's about $30 from Debra's buttons.

01:14:04.074 --> 01:14:05.909
I have some money in my bag.

01:14:06.243 --> 01:14:08.037
Here's $2...

01:14:08.162 --> 01:14:10.247
and some Bazooka Joe for karma.

01:14:10.331 --> 01:14:12.708
Here's $23 from A.J.'s expense account.

01:14:13.334 --> 01:14:15.836
Maybe you can hock this, I don't know.

01:14:18.631 --> 01:14:19.922
That's...

01:14:20.131 --> 01:14:21.507
...$3,050

01:14:22.008 --> 01:14:23.176
And...

01:14:23.259 --> 01:14:24.761
...$6,000 more.

01:14:26.387 --> 01:14:28.556
It's not about money, OK?

01:14:30.725 --> 01:14:32.185
I hate money.

01:14:37.898 --> 01:14:41.735
I thought I knew what I was doing,
but I didn't, okay?

01:14:43.904 --> 01:14:45.197
I give up.

01:14:51.327 --> 01:14:52.662
Call Mitchell.

01:14:53.371 --> 01:14:56.624
- I think we can work something out...
- No, now's the time, just call him.

01:14:59.960 --> 01:15:01.295
Wait a second.

01:15:01.337 --> 01:15:03.172
Wait, give me a couple of seconds.

01:15:04.799 --> 01:15:05.883
So the perpetrator...

01:15:05.966 --> 01:15:08.927
...will be taken to Juvenile Hall
and likely charged...

01:15:08.968 --> 01:15:12.347
...with assault with a deadly weapon
possibly even kidnapping.

01:15:12.430 --> 01:15:15.016
I saw the whole thing go down.
You see, I work here.

01:15:15.433 --> 01:15:16.559
Hey, guys, check it out.

01:15:16.643 --> 01:15:18.144
Mark's on TV!

01:15:18.186 --> 01:15:20.480
Joining us is an eyewitness to the scene.

01:15:20.605 --> 01:15:23.107
An employee of the store who saw it.
Tell us what happened.

01:15:23.941 --> 01:15:26.860
This guy here kind of wigged out and all,
but that's besides the point.

01:15:26.944 --> 01:15:31.824
We're having a get-together here tonight.
There's gonna be free admission, live music, hits, chicks.

01:15:32.408 --> 01:15:33.701
The full nine yards, man.

01:15:33.784 --> 01:15:35.994
It'll be heavy shit. Here at midnight.

01:15:36.078 --> 01:15:37.912
We're live on the air right now.
That's the story...

01:15:40.665 --> 01:15:42.959
Anybody can come. Here at midnight.
Party on, man!

01:15:43.000 --> 01:15:45.503
Damn the man! Save the Empire!

01:16:20.286 --> 01:16:22.037
We've got to make some money.

01:16:36.426 --> 01:16:39.970
You gotta invest in this
when you're young. A record is like life.

01:16:40.137 --> 01:16:41.680
It goes around and around.

01:16:42.639 --> 01:16:44.558
- How much is it?
- $80.

01:16:53.734 --> 01:16:55.110
$5 a beer.

01:16:55.194 --> 01:16:56.652
Plenty for everyone!

01:16:57.779 --> 01:16:58.863
There you go.

01:17:03.451 --> 01:17:05.787
You gotta buy something before you go in.

01:17:05.953 --> 01:17:08.414
- You wanna buy some vinyl or something?
- Hi, Mitchell.

01:17:14.419 --> 01:17:16.046
What is going on here?

01:17:16.213 --> 01:17:20.175
Why do I get the feeling
that I am being royally screwed?

01:17:21.635 --> 01:17:23.303
Because you are, Mitch.

01:17:24.888 --> 01:17:28.390
There was no money in the bag.
One of my employees needed it.

01:17:31.852 --> 01:17:32.895
Who took it?

01:17:35.105 --> 01:17:36.690
Who took my money?

01:17:38.818 --> 01:17:40.444
Mitch, this is some party.
I mean it's a hell of a turn-out.

01:17:40.528 --> 01:17:41.445
Who are you?

01:17:41.529 --> 01:17:45.031
- I'm Lucas. I still work here.
- How could I forget. We're talking...

01:17:45.114 --> 01:17:47.367
I wanted to talk to you
about this Music Town thing.

01:17:48.284 --> 01:17:52.497
Next week, you'll be the owner
of one of the many Music Towns...

01:17:52.580 --> 01:17:53.665
- Across this great land, correct?
- Yes.

01:17:53.748 --> 01:17:56.626
You like it because Music Town
raises prices, so you make more money.

01:17:56.709 --> 01:17:58.085
You're a smart boy.

01:17:58.126 --> 01:18:01.630
When Music Town comes in...
Joe is out.

01:18:01.964 --> 01:18:03.298
A.J. is out.

01:18:03.340 --> 01:18:07.553
All the beautiful little tattooed,
gum-chewing freaks are out as well.

01:18:07.636 --> 01:18:10.597
And it pretty much goes
without saying, that I'm out.

01:18:10.722 --> 01:18:13.724
Wish it had gone without saying,
but you won't shut up.

01:18:13.808 --> 01:18:16.143
What I think Lucas is trying to say...

01:18:16.310 --> 01:18:18.437
...is that I'm going to open my own store.

01:18:19.856 --> 01:18:21.732
You don't have the start-up capital.

01:18:22.108 --> 01:18:24.110
- Yes, he does.
- No, I don't.

01:18:24.986 --> 01:18:26.279
But I will.

01:18:26.696 --> 01:18:28.239
I will get it.

01:18:32.325 --> 01:18:33.368
I quit.

01:18:37.455 --> 01:18:38.540
You knew, didn't you?

01:18:38.623 --> 01:18:39.541
About what?

01:18:39.624 --> 01:18:40.876
Everything.

01:18:41.251 --> 01:18:43.169
About me,
what I wanted to do.

01:18:43.795 --> 01:18:45.671
I knew you weren't happy.

01:19:54.527 --> 01:19:57.238
Thank you for coming. 'Bye. Move along.

01:19:57.280 --> 01:19:59.407
These are on sale with a coupon, right?

01:20:12.086 --> 01:20:14.630
Doesn't anybody work in this store?

01:20:15.005 --> 01:20:16.048
I do.

01:20:23.888 --> 01:20:25.390
A.J.!

01:20:49.203 --> 01:20:53.749
Leave the merchandise, take your cup,
get out! Bug someone outside!

01:20:53.958 --> 01:20:54.959
Now!

01:20:55.835 --> 01:20:58.004
Here's all your money. Count it.

01:21:02.007 --> 01:21:04.593
I hate this place. You love it.

01:21:04.968 --> 01:21:06.636
Let me sell it to you.

01:21:07.679 --> 01:21:09.097
Cheap.

01:21:09.848 --> 01:21:11.808
Thanks, you won't regret it.

01:21:13.143 --> 01:21:15.061
Asshole.

01:21:16.563 --> 01:21:17.897
I'll take it.

01:21:18.023 --> 01:21:20.024
Give me that!

01:21:23.986 --> 01:21:24.820
You!

01:21:25.529 --> 01:21:26.613
- Take the lead.
- What?

01:21:26.864 --> 01:21:27.823
Go on.

01:21:28.949 --> 01:21:30.284
You're on.

01:22:29.923 --> 01:22:31.007
Perfect.

01:22:33.551 --> 01:22:36.221
Well, not entirely perfect.

01:22:42.351 --> 01:22:44.686
Hi. What are you doing up here?

01:22:44.853 --> 01:22:46.271
- Listen to me!
- Hello, Corey.

01:22:46.438 --> 01:22:48.774
You're so special and so talented!

01:22:48.899 --> 01:22:51.443
You have everything it takes!
More than everything it takes!

01:22:51.568 --> 01:22:55.238
And you're really stupid
because you don't know that!

01:22:56.739 --> 01:23:00.326
And I know you don't love me anymore
and I know that I blew it!

01:23:00.409 --> 01:23:02.161
And if you don't go to art school...

01:23:02.245 --> 01:23:05.790
if you don't understand how special
you are, then you know nothing.

01:23:08.793 --> 01:23:10.877
I did love you and I still...

01:23:11.169 --> 01:23:14.297
Only I didn't realize it was love
because it was more than love...

01:23:14.381 --> 01:23:17.759
and it wasn't just some stupid feeling
in my stomach.

01:23:17.843 --> 01:23:19.886
I'll never love anybody as much as you.

01:23:19.970 --> 01:23:22.889
And I hate you! Why did you wait so long?

01:23:22.931 --> 01:23:24.432
I quit.

01:23:27.518 --> 01:23:29.270
I'm going to art school...

01:23:30.521 --> 01:23:32.356
in Boston...

01:23:32.523 --> 01:23:34.233
so I can be near you.

01:23:36.902 --> 01:23:38.112
- Really?
- Yeah.

01:27:00.885 --> 01:27:03.762
That guy, whatever his name is.

01:27:04.012 --> 01:27:05.722
What's his name?

01:27:05.972 --> 01:27:08.933
That dude with the shaved head?
The liar guy?

01:27:09.351 --> 01:27:12.187
- Henry Rollins?
- Yes, the guy with tattoos all over.

01:27:12.270 --> 01:27:14.356
I admit, Henry Rollins is sort of a puss.

01:27:14.439 --> 01:27:16.858
Yeah, he's a total puss. His lyrics suck.

01:27:16.941 --> 01:27:20.152
But you can't go and put down the Misfits.

01:27:20.277 --> 01:27:22.946
They had everything it took
to be a great punk band.

01:27:23.197 --> 01:27:26.909
They had good bass lines
and strong guitar chords...

01:27:26.992 --> 01:27:28.660
even though they were only three.

01:27:28.744 --> 01:27:33.457
They didn't even compare to Primus.
They were that old school stuff.

01:27:33.499 --> 01:27:35.374
Why get into Primus?

01:27:35.458 --> 01:27:37.960
- Primus sucks.
- Primus is the new stuff.

01:27:38.169 --> 01:27:40.213
Out with the old, in with the new.

01:27:40.296 --> 01:27:43.424
Religion's a bad thing if Primus
is what's gonna come around.

01:27:43.508 --> 01:27:46.969
- What are you talking about?
- The fact that Primus has nothing.

01:27:47.053 --> 01:27:49.097
They got good bass lines. I'll admit.

01:27:49.180 --> 01:27:51.973
They have beautiful bass lines.
Six-string fretless bass...

01:27:52.015 --> 01:27:54.643
Okay, but they're not
as good as the Pixies.

01:27:54.851 --> 01:27:59.022
The Pixies have way better bass lines
than Primus.

01:27:59.064 --> 01:28:01.358
So why didn't they stick around?

01:28:01.525 --> 01:28:05.278
Because people wanted to do solo careers
and explore themselves...

01:28:05.528 --> 01:28:08.364
as single entities instead of a band.

01:28:09.865 --> 01:28:11.784
But that's like money.

01:28:11.867 --> 01:28:15.412
No, it's not about money.
What are you talking about, "money"?

01:28:15.663 --> 01:28:16.622
Yeah, it is.

01:28:20.918 --> 01:28:22.293
and everything's going to be fine...

01:28:22.502 --> 01:28:24.753
